parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shifting issues can cause the vehicle to jerk violently, leading to loss of control, accidents, or rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates to shift
revs high before shifting
shifts violently
fails to engage into gear
grinds when shifting
loses gear
and makes loud annoying noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch failure can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine shuts off while driving
the engine stalls without warning
the key can be removed from the ignition with the vehicle in gear
the anti-theft indicator illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning brake system can cause the vehicle to vibrate, emit a low humming noise, and engage involuntarily, leading to accidents, loss of control, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The brakes stick
the front end vibrates
the left wheel gets hot and locks up
the vehicle does not roll back when the foot is taken off the brake pedal on an incline
the brake pedal goes all the way to the floor
and the vehicle fails to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control unit can cause intermittent failure signals, leading to a loss of braking performance and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS control unit fails
giving intermittent failure signals
and the dealer may not have the part in stock
